<h2 style="font-size: 22px;">Mount Mercy University</h2>
<strong>Cedar Rapids, IA</strong>

<div class="infolines">
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers credit for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-green">Yes</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
    <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class="span10">Offers placement into higher-level courses for AP Exams</div>
        <div class="span2 alignRight">
                <div class="short-status-red">No</div>
        </div>
    </div>    
</div>


<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Entering freshmen who have successfully completed college-level courses in high school and who earn a rating of three, four or five on the Advanced Placement Test of the College Entrance Examination Board will be given credit for an equivalent college-level course. Students seeking admission to Mount Mercy may be considered for advanced placement by having a report of their examination sent to the Registrar's Office.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.mtmercy.edu/schedules-and-catalog" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

